575
00:36:46,419 --> 00:36:49,589
God, I get so frustrated,
I just wanna do something.

576
00:36:49,714 --> 00:36:52,216
- Like what?
- I don't know. Something.!

577
00:36:52,341 --> 00:36:54,927
Something other than what
I'm supposed to do.

578
00:37:03,895 --> 00:37:06,647
If you look now, you'll see
how people are just opening up...

579
00:37:06,772 --> 00:37:08,649
allowing this car to pass freely.

580
00:37:08,774 --> 00:37:11,444
It's amazing that this far
the police haven't been able to stop him.

581
00:37:11,569 --> 00:37:14,822
Oh, wonderful. Here comes the circus.

582
00:37:14,947 --> 00:37:16,908
What is she doing here?

583
00:37:18,326 --> 00:37:21,245
I happen to be
the girl's mother, thank you.

584
00:37:21,329 --> 00:37:23,831
- How's my baby?
- She seems just fine, Mrs. Voss.

585
00:37:23,915 --> 00:37:26,918
- We're doing everything we can.
- Ha. That's a laugh.

586
00:37:27,001 --> 00:37:30,046
What's the matter, Dalton? Haven't you
been able to buy things right this time?

587
00:37:30,171 --> 00:37:31,964
Dalton, don't listen to that.

588
00:37:32,048 --> 00:37:35,384
- The truth hurts, doesn't it?
- Frances, I am not in the mood.

589
00:37:35,510 --> 00:37:38,095
Dalton, you were never in the mood.

590
00:37:38,179 --> 00:37:40,473
- I never!
- I never did either, married to him.

591
00:37:40,598 --> 00:37:44,810
Folks, come on now. I know this tension
is unsettling, but please.

592
00:37:44,936 --> 00:37:48,564
This bickering amongst yourselves
doesn't get us anything.

593
00:37:48,689 --> 00:37:52,610
- Hodges, get the Vosses and Mr., uh...
- MacEnernie.

594
00:37:52,735 --> 00:37:55,279
- MacEnernie some coffee.
- Yes, sir.

595
00:37:57,031 --> 00:37:59,951
Chief, there's a Mr. AriJosephson
on the phone.

596
00:38:00,034 --> 00:38:03,037
- He's Hammond's attorney from San Francisco.
