00:58:28,304 --> 00:58:30,223
And standing here with me
are Will and Dale.

919
00:58:30,306 --> 00:58:32,391
They are the drivers
of the green monster van.

920
00:58:32,517 --> 00:58:34,435
- Tell me, gentlemen...
- Monster truck.

921
00:58:34,560 --> 00:58:38,231
Monster truck. What possessed you to
take such radical and desperate measures...

922
00:58:38,356 --> 00:58:40,233
to stop the BMWyourselves?

923
00:58:40,358 --> 00:58:45,404
Oh! Dude! We are just doing our duty
as Americans. Right, Will?

924
00:58:45,530 --> 00:58:48,950
That's right. And that's not the first time
we've had to take matters into our own hands.

925
00:58:49,075 --> 00:58:51,953
Mark my words,
they'll be pulling over soon.

926
00:58:52,078 --> 00:58:53,955
We really scared them.
Didn't we? Didn't we?

927
00:58:54,080 --> 00:58:56,165
- Did you see the look on their faces?
- Sure did.

928
00:58:56,290 --> 00:58:59,377
- Whoa!
- And we'd be happy to tell anyone about it. Anyone.

929
00:58:59,460 --> 00:59:02,171
- Anytime!
- On-On Oprah. Or Geraldo.

930
00:59:02,296 --> 00:59:04,924
- Or SallyJesse. Or any-any...
- Larry King. Larry King.

931
00:59:05,007 --> 00:59:07,051
Yeah. Or any of those shows.

932
00:59:07,134 --> 00:59:11,347
That's right. And you can usually find us
at Big Willy's Dirty Dogs. Most times.

933
00:59:11,430 --> 00:59:13,349
My name is Will, and this is Dale.

934
00:59:13,432 --> 00:59:15,935
And we've been through a lot ofheavy stuff
in that truck before.

935
00:59:16,018 --> 00:59:19,147
- Monster madness, dude.
- Major monster madness.

936
00:59:19,272 --> 00:59:21,440
- Gentlemen, please.
- What? But-But...

937
00:59:21,566 --> 00:59:23,776
- We're not fooling around! We're not fooling around!
- Get in the back.

938
00:59:23,901 --> 00:59:28,906
Sometimes you got to take the bull by
the horns! We're American citizens!

939
00:59:28,990 --> 00:59:31,742
And there you have it. Who says the great
American hero is a thing of the past?

940
00:59:31,826 --> 00:59:35,454
- Back to you, Rocky...
- I hope you can see this, Bill and Wendy.

941
00:59:35,580 --> 00:59:39,458
It's like a circus down there.

942
00:59:39,542 --> 00:59:41,836
You know, Byron, it's easy for us
reporting this story...

943
00:59:41,961 --> 00:59:45,131
to forget there's a very scared
little girl inside that car.

944
00:59:45,256 --> 00:59:47,341
We can only imagine,
as this chase continues...

945
00:59:47,466 --> 00:59:50,761
the horror young Natalie Voss
is experiencing right now.

946
00:59:52,263 --> 00:59:54,265
Oh, shit.

947
00:59:54,390 --> 00:59:57,351
- Just-Just hold still.
- It stings.

948
00:59:58,686 --> 01:00:02,607
- Mm!
- I don't want it to get infected.

949
01:00:02,690 --> 01:00:05,985
- I'm so sorry about this.
- As you should be.

950
01:00:13,034 --> 01:00:16,120
- What are you doing?
- You're sweating.

951
01:00:25,046 --> 01:00:28,883
I've never met anybody
quite like you, Jack.

952
01:00:29,008 --> 01:00:31,052
I wish things were different.

953
01:00:31,177 --> 01:00:34,347
I'm really a pretty likable guy
when I'm not a fugitive.

954
01:00:34,430 --> 01:00:37,225
I wish things were different too.

955
01:00:37,350 --> 01:00:39,227
Isn't it funny how people meet?

956
01:00:39,352 --> 01:00:42,230
I mean, they can come from
two totally different worlds...

957
01:00:42,355 --> 01:00:45,691
and never even know
each other exists.

958
01:00:45,817 --> 01:00:50,988
And then one day they meet
and their lives are never the same.

959
01:00:51,072 --> 01:00:53,699
- Are you married?
- No.

960
01:00:56,035 --> 01:00:57,912
Do you have a girlfriend?

961
01:00:58,037 --> 01:01:00,915
No, I don't have a girlfriend.

962
01:01:03,000 --> 01:01:05,002
And it's true that...

963
01:01:05,127 --> 01:01:09,674
you haven't been with a woman
in a couple of years?

964
01:01:09,799 --> 01:01:11,759
It's true, yeah.

965
01:01:14,053 --> 01:01:17,348
If all this doesn't work out,
you'll go back to prison, right?

966
01:01:17,431 --> 01:01:19,392
Probably.

967
01:01:23,020 --> 01:01:25,231
So it's conceivable that...

968
01:01:27,733 --> 01:01:30,903
you'd never be with a woman
ever again, right?

969
01:01:31,028 --> 01:01:32,989
Right.

970
01:01:38,077 --> 01:01:40,037
What are you doing?

971
01:01:42,123 --> 01:01:44,208
Falling in love with you.

972
01:01:53,509 --> 01:01:57,680
Natalie, you can't...
We can't do this.

973
01:01:58,973 --> 01:02:01,267
I can't help it.

974
01:02:01,392 --> 01:02:04,687
We may never have
this chance again.

975
01:02:32,840 --> 01:02:34,967
Wait a second.
Wait a second.

976
01:02:53,277 --> 01:02:56,948
Can't see the road.

977
01:02:57,031 --> 01:03:00,993
There it is. There's the road.

978
01:03:06,874 --> 01:03:10,127
Ten more miles, do or die.

979
01:03:10,211 --> 01:03:12,338
What the hell is he
swerving all over for?

980
01:04:22,909 --> 01:04:24,785
I just figured it all out.

981
01:04:24,911 --> 01:04:27,830
It's just like you said.
I'm your insurance policy.

982
01:04:27,914 --> 01:04:29,832
What are you talking about?

983
01:04:29,916 --> 01:04:32,919
Well, as long as I'm your hostage,
they can't get to you.

984
01:04:33,044 --> 01:04:35,129
You can demand a ransom
from my father...

985
01:04:35,254 --> 01:04:39,091
we'll take the money, we'll escape to Mexico
just like you said.

986
01:04:39,175 --> 01:04:42,512
Hey, hey, hey.
Hold on a minute here, Patty Hearst.

987
01:04:42,637 --> 01:04:46,265
- What?
- On second thought, maybe Mexico ain't such a hot idea.

988
01:04:46,390 --> 01:04:49,060
We'll have to wait in line at the border
while they check the trunk for illegal fruit.

989
01:04:49,143 --> 01:04:53,439
- I mean, come on.
- No, I'm completely serious. They'll never be able to get us.

990
01:04:53,523 --> 01:04:57,443
I'm your hostage. There's no way they could
possibly think we're in this together.

991
01:04:57,568 --> 01:05:00,696
It's getting close.
It's getting real close.

992
01:05:00,780 --> 01:05:03,699
Subject vehicle, red BMW...

993
01:05:03,783 --> 01:05:06,702
now approaching
with suspect and hostage.

994
01:05:06,786 --> 01:05:10,498
- All officers take your positions.
- Move! Come on! Come on!

995
01:05:12,291 --> 01:05:15,545
Prepare to engage suspect.

996
01:05:19,090 --> 01:05:23,010
All emergency services
remain in position.

997
01:05:23,135 --> 01:05:25,304
Fire, be ready with foam.

998
01:05:25,388 --> 01:05:27,348
Paramedics, stand by.

999
01:05:30,893 --> 01:05:34,438
- This could actually work.
- Yes, it's gonna work. It's gonna work.

1000
01:05:34,564 --> 01:05:37,942
- All right.
- I know this beautiful spot in Cabo San Lucas...

1001
01:05:38,025 --> 01:05:40,736
where the beaches are gorgeous.

1002
01:05:40,820 --> 01:05:42,905
God, this is so romantic.

1003
01:05:42,989 --> 01:05:46,576
Have you noticed that there's no other cars
on the road anymore?

1004
01:05:46,701 --> 01:05:48,661
Cars?

1005
01:05:48,744 --> 01:05:53,499
Attention.! Subject vehicle
is 500 yards and approaching fast.

1006
01:05:54,959 --> 01:05:57,503
All personnel stand clear
of the barricade.

1007
01:05:58,754 --> 01:06:00,506
Oh, my God.

1008
01:06:00,590 --> 01:06:02,508
- Strap in!
- Oh, shit!

1009
01:06:02,592 --> 01:06:04,969
Strap in! Hang on!

1010
01:06:12,059 --> 01:06:16,314
Maybe this whole thing
wasn't such a hot idea after all.

1011
01:06:16,397 --> 01:06:18,483
This is it!

1012
01:06:18,608 --> 01:06:22,111
- This is more exciting than election night!
- Box 'em in! Box 'em in!

1013
01:06:22,195 --> 01:06:24,780
- Do something!
- Like what?

1014
01:06:24,864 --> 01:06:27,033
I don't know! Anything!

1015
01:06:29,869 --> 01:06:32,205
- What are you doing?
- Anything!

1016
01:06:34,665 --> 01:06:36,667
Holy shit!

1017
01:06:47,345 --> 01:06:51,224
This is unheard-of!
The surprise roadblock has backfired!

1018
01:06:51,349 --> 01:06:56,562
- Hammond's outsmarted the cops!
- Get in control out there! Stop that damn car!

1019
01:07:09,450 --> 01:07:12,161
Don't panic!

1020
01:07:19,544 --> 01:07:22,547
- The tension is unbearable!
- Shit! - Yes, sir!

1021
01:07:22,672 --> 01:07:26,717
- Stay close to your sets.!
- Oh! I'm gonna die! I'm gonna die!

1022
01:07:26,843 --> 01:07:29,220
You're not gonna die! Relax!

1023
01:07:33,432 --> 01:07:35,935
Keep shooting!
Think of my Emmy!

1024
01:07:42,942 --> 01:07:47,905
Take your stinking paws off me,
you damn dirty ape!

1025
01:07:47,989 --> 01:07:50,908
Monkeys.

1026
01:07:50,992 --> 01:07:52,952
Fix this damn thing.

1027
01:08:00,585 --> 01:08:02,587
Whoo!

1028
01:08:30,573 --> 01:08:34,494
Hammond seems to be...
Bill, Wendy, can you see this?

1029
01:08:34,619 --> 01:08:38,331
Hammond is leading the pursuit in
a giant game of ring-around-the-rosy.

1030
01:08:38,414 --> 01:08:41,959
Jack, you anti-hero, if you're
going to get away, get away now.

1031
01:08:42,043 --> 01:08:44,879
Bill, this is really ridiculous. It's pretty clear
now that this guy, Jack Hammond...

1032
01:08:45,004 --> 01:08:46,964
is just toying with the police.

1033
01:08:47,048 --> 01:08:50,134
I hope they put him away
for a long time.

1034
01:08:50,259 --> 01:08:53,346
- You are dead serious about going with me?
- Serious as a heart attack.

1035
01:08:53,471 --> 01:08:56,265
You are absolutely, positively,
100% sure about this?

1036
01:08:56,349 --> 01:08:59,811
I have never been more sure
about anything in my entire life.

1037
01:09:05,775 --> 01:09:08,694
- We'll be fugitives.
- Sounds exciting.

1038
01:09:08,778 --> 01:09:11,322
- You won't be Natalie Voss anymore.
- Who the hell is she anyway?

1039
01:09:11,405 --> 01:09:13,699
I don't know. I don't know. But you're
going to give up everything for me?

1040
01:09:13,825 --> 01:09:16,828
Don't flatter yourself.
I'm doing it for me too.

1041
01:09:16,953 --> 01:09:18,871
Of course you are.

1042
01:10:12,008 --> 01:10:13,968
This is it.!

1043
01:10:16,804 --> 01:10:18,723
Let go of the girl, Hammond!

1044
01:10:42,914 --> 01:10:45,291
What are you doing?
Let's keep going.

1045
01:10:45,416 --> 01:10:47,293
Look, Natalie,
if I had things my way...

1046
01:10:47,418 --> 01:10:50,296
you'd be the girl I'd run away
to paradise with.

1047
01:10:50,421 --> 01:10:52,715
But I'm gonna be your hostage.

1048
01:10:52,798 --> 01:10:55,259
Natalie, it's over.

1049
01:10:57,136 --> 01:11:00,765
I can't let you ruin your life
because of me.

1050
01:11:02,767 --> 01:11:07,104
- I think it's time for you to go home now.
- You can't mean that.

1051
01:11:10,066 --> 01:11:12,610
You know, until yesterday...

1052
01:11:12,693 --> 01:11:16,656
the worst thing I ever did in
my whole life was cheat on a biology exam.

1053
01:11:18,157 --> 01:11:20,618
And now I'm a car thief...

1054
01:11:20,743 --> 01:11:22,870
a kidnapper...

1055
01:11:22,995 --> 01:11:25,957
cop-shooter, police-evader.

1056
01:11:27,792 --> 01:11:29,752
I can't do this to you.

1057
01:11:31,337 --> 01:11:34,507
I can't make you
part of this anymore.

1058
01:11:36,676 --> 01:11:38,678
I care about you too much.

1059
01:11:41,305 --> 01:11:45,643
Besides, I can't hold you
hostage anymore.

1060
01:11:45,726 --> 01:11:47,687
We ate the gun.

1061
01:11:48,980 --> 01:11:51,149
But you have the real gun.

1062
01:11:51,232 --> 01:11:53,192
Uh...

1063
01:11:55,069 --> 01:11:57,321
real guns make me nervous.

1064
01:12:02,869 --> 01:12:05,121
I do better with the candy ones.

1065
01:12:05,204 --> 01:12:07,331
Jack, you're innocent.

1066
01:12:09,417 --> 01:12:11,377
We can make this work.

1067
01:12:16,883 --> 01:12:20,887
You... You're really something.
You know that?

1068
01:12:23,431 --> 01:12:26,642
- Thank you.
- For what?

1069
01:12:26,726 --> 01:12:28,853
For believing in me.

1070
01:12:28,936 --> 01:12:31,939
Let the girl go now, Hammond!

1071
01:12:32,064 --> 01:12:35,026
It's been a hell of a ride, huh, kid?

1072
01:12:36,611 --> 01:12:39,780
What say you, uh...

1073
01:12:39,906 --> 01:12:42,867
step out of the car
and walk away from me?

1074
01:12:43,951 --> 01:12:46,704
- I'll be fine.
- You come with me.

1075
01:12:46,787 --> 01:12:50,875
You first.
I'm right behind you.

1076
01:13:41,509 --> 01:13:44,178
Miss Voss.!
Miss Voss.! Okay, stay down.

1077
01:13:44,303 --> 01:13:46,305
Oh, you're a lucky girl.
You're a lucky girl.

1078
01:13:46,430 --> 01:13:49,100
Just get behind the door there.
Just get right behind the door there.

1079
01:13:49,183 --> 01:13:51,144
We will take care of him.
Don't worry.

1080
01:13:51,269 --> 01:13:53,312
Boy, I hope he tries something now.

1081
01:13:53,437 --> 01:13:57,150
Come on, Hammond.
Just give me one reason.

1082
01:14:01,320 --> 01:14:06,075
Way to go, Jack.
Way to go.

1083
01:14:06,159 --> 01:14:09,287
Come on, Hammond!
You're in a no-win situation!

1084
01:14:09,370 --> 01:14:11,747
Put your hands out of the car
where I can see them!

1085
01:16:08,531 --> 01:16:11,117
- Stand up, Hammond.! Stand up.!
- Get up.! Turn around, turn around.!

1086
01:16:11,242 --> 01:16:14,412
Turn around.! Hands on your head.!
On your head.!

1087
01:16:14,495 --> 01:16:16,455
You know the drill.

1088
01:16:16,539 --> 01:16:22,420
- You got him? You got him.
- We got you now, my friend. Take it nice and easy now.

1089
01:16:22,503 --> 01:16:24,964
- Eyes forward.
- Nice and easy. That hand down!

1090
01:16:25,047 --> 01:16:28,384
- Nice and easy.
- They're on him!

1091
01:16:28,467 --> 01:16:30,136
Damn.! I'd love to kill you.!

1092
01:16:32,054 --> 01:16:34,307
- What the...
- You got it?

1093
01:16:34,432 --> 01:16:38,102
- Cigarettes.
- Ha!

1094
01:16:39,270 --> 01:16:41,481
I wish you'd run.

1095
01:16:41,606 --> 01:16:44,400
I'd love to kill you.
I would love to kill you.

1096
01:16:44,484 --> 01:16:46,486
But you can't run,
'cause you're busted.!

1097
01:16:46,569 --> 01:16:49,363
Eyes forward!

1098
01:16:51,240 --> 01:16:54,160
I don't like you.

1099
01:16:56,454 --> 01:16:59,499
Keep your gun on him.!
Keep your gun on him.!

1100
01:17:00,875 --> 01:17:04,795
Ain't nothing gonna
help you, Hammond.

1101
01:17:25,566 --> 01:17:27,527
I'm sorry about all this, Mr. Voss.

1102
01:17:28,903 --> 01:17:31,322
Your daughter is a fine young lady.

1103
01:17:36,369 --> 01:17:39,622
This is the money shot, Ned.
The father-daughter reunion.

1104
01:17:40,873 --> 01:17:44,210
- Beautiful.
- He didn't hurt me. He's innocent.

1105
01:17:44,293 --> 01:17:46,337
- He's innocent!
- Later.

1106
01:17:46,462 --> 01:17:51,008
That really was funny. That was really funny
how that guy smacked you.

1107
01:17:51,133 --> 01:17:52,885
Give him his rights.

1108
01:17:52,969 --> 01:17:55,638
Now that we're spending
all this quality time together...

1109
01:17:55,721 --> 01:17:57,640
let me tell you about your rights.

1110
01:17:57,723 --> 01:17:59,559
You have the right to remain silent.

1111
01:17:59,684 --> 01:18:02,478
Anything you say can and will be
used against you in a court oflaw.

1112
01:18:02,562 --> 01:18:04,564
If you do not have an attorney,
one will be assigned to you.

1113
01:18:04,647 --> 01:18:06,983
Do you understand all the rights
I have read to you right now?

1114
01:18:07,066 --> 01:18:09,152
- Yes.
- Good boy. Now shut up.!

1115
01:18:09,235 --> 01:18:13,072
- How's it look? How's it look?
- It's beautiful.

1116
01:18:13,156 --> 01:18:16,409
Know what happens to pretty boys like you
when they go to prison after the lights go out?

1117
01:18:16,492 --> 01:18:20,663
"Oh, girlfriend.! Oh, girlfriend.!"

1118
01:18:20,746 --> 01:18:23,708
Shots fired.!

1119
01:18:27,420 --> 01:18:30,047
- Uncuff him now!
- What? What the hell?

1120
01:18:30,131 --> 01:18:33,676
What in God's name?
Have you lost your mind, young lady?

1121
01:18:33,759 --> 01:18:36,095
I said uncuff
Jack Hammond now!

1122
01:18:36,220 --> 01:18:40,766
Come on, Miss Voss. Put the gun down.
You don't know what you're doing.

1123
01:18:40,892 --> 01:18:42,894
This guy's brainwashed you.
Now come on.

1124
01:18:42,977 --> 01:18:48,191
- Ned, get a shot of this!
- Natalie, stop embarrassing me.

1125
01:18:48,274 --> 01:18:51,110
Do it, or I'll blow his brains out
all over live TV.

1126
01:18:51,235 --> 01:18:54,739
Miss Voss, don't do it.
You're confused. He's confused you.

1127
01:18:54,864 --> 01:18:56,866
- It's very confusing.
- Don't move!

1128
01:18:56,949 --> 01:19:00,036
I said, don't move.!

1129
01:19:14,550 --> 01:19:16,469
I mean business.

1130
01:19:16,552 --> 01:19:20,807
Goddamn it.! Would you think about what
you're doing.! This guy's a scumbag.!

1131
01:19:20,932 --> 01:19:24,310
He doesn't want you! He's only using you!
Come on! Put the gun down!

1132
01:19:24,435 --> 01:19:26,395
Back away from Jack now!

1133
01:19:38,199 --> 01:19:41,911
- You've gone completely crazy. You know that?
- Thanks for noticing.

1134
01:19:41,994 --> 01:19:45,122
How do you plan to get us
out of this one?

1135
01:19:45,206 --> 01:19:47,166
Watch me and weep.

1136
01:19:51,671 --> 01:19:53,840
It takes all kinds, Dalt.

1137
01:19:55,216 --> 01:19:57,301
Okay, Bill, Wendy,
I hope you're getting this.

1138
01:19:57,426 --> 01:20:00,346
They are walking directly
towards the helicopter...

1139
01:20:00,429 --> 01:20:03,141
and they're staring at me
like a couple of crazed dogs.

1140
01:20:03,224 --> 01:20:05,518
I'm gonna try to get a word
from them if I can.

1141
01:20:05,643 --> 01:20:07,645
This is unbelievable,
ladies and gentlemen. This...

1142
01:20:07,728 --> 01:20:10,481
- Oh, my... - Get out of there.
- Let's go, pal. Let's go.

1143
01:20:10,565 --> 01:20:12,775
- I'm being asked...
- Come on! Go! Go!

1144
01:20:12,859 --> 01:20:15,486
I'm being removed from my own helicopter,
ladies and gentlemen.

1145
01:20:15,611 --> 01:20:17,363
The first margarita's on me.

1146
01:20:21,784 --> 01:20:24,537
Not so fast.

1147
01:20:24,662 --> 01:20:27,623
Did you get it?
Did you? Yes!

1148
01:20:29,208 --> 01:20:32,295
I want big!
I want cinematic!

1149
01:20:32,378 --> 01:20:35,047
I want...
I want Pennebaker.!

1150
01:20:35,173 --> 01:20:38,551
Get this. Get the copter.

1151
01:27:47,313 --> 01:27:49,232
You smell that?

1152
01:27:49,315 --> 01:27:51,234
Do you smell that?

1153
01:27:51,317 --> 01:27:54,153
Nothing else in the world
smells like that, son.

1154
01:27:54,237 --> 01:27:56,531
I love the smell of napalm
in the morning.

1155
01:27:56,656 --> 01:27:58,658
You know one day
we had a hill bombed.

1156
01:27:58,783 --> 01:28:01,994
When I walked out, we didn't find
one of them. Not one stinking dink body.

1157
01:28:02,078 --> 01:28:06,415
But that smell.
That gasoline smell. The whole hill.

1158
01:28:06,499 --> 01:28:09,585
It smelled like... victory.

1159
01:28:11,254 --> 01:28:27,937
Subtitles by Fred

